com.amazonaws.services.simpleworkflow.flow.annotations

Annotation Type Execute


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Execute
    @Execute annotation is used on methods of interface annotated with Workflow to specify the entry-point for WorkflowType. @Execute method can only have void or Promise return types. Parameters of type Promise are not allowed.
    Author:
    fateev, samar
    See Also:
    Workflow, WorkflowWorker

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      String version
      Required version of the workflow type.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String name
      Optional name of the workflow type.

    • Element Detail

        Optional name of the workflow type. When missing defaults to the annotated method name. Maximum length is 256 characters.
